Advance information and notice
In the case of construction projects with construction services to be awarded throughout Europe, the public contractor has to inform interested companies about the planned contracts in advance of the tender.
Preliminary information and announcements form an important basis for a Europe-wide competition.
Requirements of EU law and the prevention of corruption
The preliminary information should contain the essential public procurement data on the planned construction projects.
They are required for construction projects where the estimated total value of the contract reaches or exceeds the EU threshold and where the client wants to shorten the offer periods of open or non-open procedures.
In notices, the client must provide binding details of the construction contracts to be awarded throughout Europe.
