Regulations of German and Czech Public Procurement Law
The same or similar rules
The Procurement Documents on the basis of which the companies are to draw up their bids are, in principle, only to be sent by the contracting authority.
Freelancers involved in the award procedure are not allowed to carry out this task.
The contracting authority must ensure that all applicants receive the same information during the bidding phase.
In the event of a lack of clarity on the tender documents or other questions relating to the tender, only the contracting authority may provide information to the applicants.
Freelancers entrusted with the preparation of the tender documents are not allowed to provide information.
During the entire offer phase, it is necessary to prevent contact between the authorised freelancers and the applicants.
Freelancers must not be allowed to become a hub of the award procedure, through which contacts with anti-competitive consequences can be established.
