The German regulations stipulate that all open offers must be marked in such a way that subsequent changes and additions are prevented.
The offers are usually marked by perforations with the date of the opening date. They are to be kept secret after the opening date and may only be made available to the persons directly responsible for the processing.
The Czech regulations do not exist.
If only one bid is received in a procurement procedure in the Czech Republic, it must not be opened and returned unvalued.
There is no such regulation in Germany. If only one offer is received, it must be opened and then evaluated.
