If a bidder makes a request for review within the information period, the conclusion of a contract is only possible after the final decision in the review process.
Companies can also have the award decision reviewed by an independent court as part of this review process.
The review procedure is intended to ensure the legal protection of companies and to encourage the client to comply with public procurement law throughout the award procedure.
In order to do so, he must document the procedure sufficiently.
Regulations of German and Czech Public Procurement Law
The same or similar rules
Both countries have implemented EU rules on information and verification procedures.
In both countries, the awarding authority has to decide on the award of the contract.
However, it must not deviate arbitrarily from the result of a proper examination and evaluation of the offers.
The client is to place the order within the announced surcharge period,
Also because the bidders are no longer bound by their bids after the deadline.
In the case of open and non-open procedures or public and limited tenders, the client may not deviate from the content of the offer when concluding the contract.
The underperforming bidders must be informed promptly of the award decision and the reasons for not taking their bids into account.
Procurement procedures may only be cancelled under certain conditions, e.g. if the bid prices are excessive or the bids do not meet the requirements of the tender.
Diverging regulations
In the Czech Republic, there is a 10-day or 15-day obligation to provide information and to wait for an award, even in the case of construction services not to be awarded throughout Europe.
In Germany, these requirements apply only to the area of EU-wide contracts.
In the case of the other procedures in Germany, bidders can only be informed of the award decision after the award has been granted.
In the Czech Republic, a tender procedure has to be cancelled if only one offer has been received or only one offer has been evaluated.
In Germany, the contract is to be awarded even in the case of only one valuable offer, provided that it complies with the conditions of the tender and is economical.
Key test results
BRH
In the case of the audited contracts, there were only a few complaints at the conclusion of the procurement procedures.
In some cases, companies have already received letters of order for EU-wide contracts before the expiry of the information deadlines, which may lead to the invalidity of the contract.
In individual cases, letters of order, following open procedures, also contain content that deviates from the content of the offer, such as changed dates.
In several cases, the contracting authorities did not comply with the additional periods.
In the case of an open procedure, a contracting authority therefore awarded the contract to the second most advantageous offer, since a company with a 50% cheaper offer was no longer prepared to carry out the services at the originally offered price after the expiry of the surcharge period.
